- `gcd_while_modified`, `gcd_recursive_modified`, `gcd_stein_u64_modified` â€” divisibility-postcondition exists but proof is `Nat.gcd_rec`-driven, not bit-mask-driven; misleading anchor.
- `clamp_modified`, `min_modified`, `is_zero_modified` â€” total trivial functions; no partial-operator or bit-trick content.
- `clever_044_triangle_area_modified` â€” signed arithmetic and div-by-static-literal; target is unsigned with bit-trick.
- `sqrt_u64_modified` â€” log2/initial-guess shift overlaps mildly with `align_m1`, but the proof is dominated by Babylonian Newton convergence, not relevant here.
- `largest_divisor_modified` â€” divisibility postcondition is recursion-witness-based, not bit-mask-based.
- `recursion_example`, `while_example`, `gcd_while_modified` â€” control-flow templates; target has no loops/recursion.
- `is_zero_modified`, `slice_get_u64_modified` â€” too narrow; useful idioms already covered by `is_size_align_valid_usize_modified`.
- `max_odd_part_modified` â€” composes `trailing_zeros` in a loop; target has no loop, simpler shape already covered by picks #1 and #2.

